CLEAR is called when CPR is in progress and an electrical shock is going to be administered to the patient. If someone is touching the patient (or frame of the cart or bed) there is chance that that person may get a shock as well. So CLEAR is said loudly so that people can back away and stay safe. Applies whether using a defibrillator or an AED—one should NOT be touching the patient when they're being shocked.

